Sentencas: Oxygen electroreduction kinetics and electrochemical performance of the Pr6O11-impregnated Sr2Fe1.5Mo0.5O6-delta - Ce0.8Sm0.2O1.9 (SFM-SDC) cathode have been first studied.
Titulo: Influence of Pr6O11 on oxygen electroreduction kinetics and electrochemical performance of Sr2Fe1.5Mo0.5O6-δ based cathode

Sentencas: By means of distribution of relaxation times and non-linear least squares analysis of impedance spectra were shown that the addition of Pr6O11 into the cathode leads to the increase in the rate of the low-frequency step.
Titulo: Influence of Pr6O11 on oxygen electroreduction kinetics and electrochemical performance of Sr2Fe1.5Mo0.5O6-δ based cathode

Sentencas: It is suggested that the observed phenomenon is associated with the increase in the rate of surface oxygen exchange.
Titulo: Influence of Pr6O11 on oxygen electroreduction kinetics and electrochemical performance of Sr2Fe1.5Mo0.5O6-δ based cathode

Sentencas: It is shown that the introduction of praseodymium oxide into the cathode results in a decrease in the area specific polarization resistances of the cathode at equilibrium potentials from 0.23 to 0.06 Omega cm(2) at 800 degrees C in air.
Titulo: Influence of Pr6O11 on oxygen electroreduction kinetics and electrochemical performance of Sr2Fe1.5Mo0.5O6-δ based cathode

Sentencas: The maximum power density of symmetrical solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) with impregnated SFM-SDC electrodes and supporting 760 mu m La0.85Sr0.15Ga0.85Mg0.15O3-delta electrolyte without buffer/barrier and collector layers under air/wet hydrogen (dry CH4) condition was about 0.5 (0.26)
Titulo: Influence of Pr6O11 on oxygen electroreduction kinetics and electrochemical performance of Sr2Fe1.5Mo0.5O6-δ based cathode
Influence of Pr6O11 on oxygen electroreduction kinetics and electrochemical performance of Sr2Fe1.5Mo0.5O6-δ based cathode

Sentencas: The overvoltage of the cathode was higher than that of the anode under air/wet hydrogen and vice versa when methane was supplied to the anode.
Titulo: Influence of Pr6O11 on oxygen electroreduction kinetics and electrochemical performance of Sr2Fe1.5Mo0.5O6-δ based cathode

Sentencas: The obtained results elucidate that the impregnated SFM-SDC is a promising cathode for SOFC application.
Titulo: Influence of Pr6O11 on oxygen electroreduction kinetics and electrochemical performance of Sr2Fe1.5Mo0.5O6-δ based cathode
